<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p><strong>Road information:</strong> The hospital is well signposted from Truro town centre and from the A390 which runs immediately outside the hospital.</p><br/><p><strong>Park &amp; Ride: </strong>A park and ride service is available at Threemilestone.  <a href="http://www.parkfortruro.org.uk">Click here</a> for details.</p><br/><p><strong>Bus information: </strong>The Royal Cornwall Hospital is on a number of bus routes and buses stop outside the main entrances. Advice on bus times is available from:</p><br/><ul><br/><li><a href="http://www.travelinesw.com/swe/XSLT_TRIP_REQUEST2?language=en&amp;timeOffset=15">Traveline</a> on 0870 608 2608 </li><br/><li>First Devon &amp; Cornwall: 0845 600 1420 </li><br/><li>Western Greyhound: <strong>01637 871871</strong> </li><br/></ul><br/><p><strong>Rail information:</strong> Truro railway station is approximately two miles away. There are bus links to the hospital and taxis are available for hire.  <a href="http://www.nationalrail.co.uk">Train information</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>During busy periods, particular afternoons, car parking on the site can be difficult and we cannot guarantee the availability of spaces. Please allow plenty of time before your appointment to find a parking space. <br/><br/>See our website for more information and details of charges.</p>
